Round 1: 
[Patient] "What foods can help me manage my heart failure?" 
[Educator] "Try to eat more fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and lean proteins." 

Round 2: 
[Patient] "Are there any specific foods I should avoid?" 
[Educator] "Limit high-sodium foods like processed meats, canned soups, and fast food." 

Round 3: 
[Patient] "What about drinks? What should I be drinking?" 
[Educator] "Drink plenty of water and limit sugary drinks and alcohol." 

Round 4: 
[Patient] "I love fried foods, can I still eat them?" 
[Educator] "It's best to limit fried foods as they can be high in unhealthy fats." 

Round 5: 
[Patient] "Any tips for eating healthy on a tight budget?" 
[Educator] "Look for sales on frozen fruits and veggies, and buy in bulk when you can."